	<article id="post-12838" class="post-12838 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general tag-employee-engagement tag-employee-relations tag-reader-question tag-strategic-hr">
				<header class="entry-header">
			
						<h1 class="entry-title">
				<a href="https://upstarthr.com/does-hr-care-more-about-employees-or-protecting-the-company-reader-question/" rel="bookmark">Does #HR care more about employees or protecting the company? [Reader Question]</a>
			</h1>
										<div class="comments-link">
					<a href="https://upstarthr.com/does-hr-care-more-about-employees-or-protecting-the-company-reader-question/#respond"><span class="leave-reply">Leave a reply</span></a>				</div><!-- .comments-link -->
					</header><!-- .entry-header -->

				<div class="entry-content">
			<p><em>I love <a href="https://upstarthr.com/tag/reader-question/">answering questions from readers</a>, because they encourage me to explore topics I might otherwise not touch on, such as today&#8217;s discussion. Have a question of your own? Share it and I&#8217;ll try to work it into the schedule!</em></p>
<blockquote><p>Does HR care more about the employees or protecting the company?</p></blockquote>
<h3>HR&#8217;s Primary Role</h3>
<p>When someone is hired into the HR profession, their primary role is to support the &#8220;people&#8221; functions of the company, such as hiring, training, and retaining employees. It&#8217;s funny if you think about that being the primary responsibility set, because we know that managers select candidates, often recommend workers for development, and are the reason that <a href="https://upstarthr.com/7-hidden-reasons-employees-leave-book-review/">80-90% of workers leave the organization</a>, Regardless, that&#8217;s our job: tie the business objectives with the people process objectives to the degree we can.  <a href="https://upstarthr.com/does-hr-care-more-about-employees-or-protecting-the-company-reader-question/#more-12838" class="more-link">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&rarr;</span></a></p>
					</div><!-- .entry-content -->
		
		<footer class="entry-meta">
			This entry was posted in <a href="https://upstarthr.com/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a> and tagged <a href="https://upstarthr.com/tag/employee-engagement/" rel="tag">Employee Engagement</a>, <a href="https://upstarthr.com/tag/employee-relations/" rel="tag">Employee Relations</a>, <a href="https://upstarthr.com/tag/reader-question/" rel="tag">reader question</a>, <a href="https://upstarthr.com/tag/strategic-hr/" rel="tag">Strategic HR</a> on <a href="https://upstarthr.com/does-hr-care-more-about-employees-or-protecting-the-company-reader-question/" title="7:39 am" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2019-01-22T07:39:35+00:00">January 22, 2019</time></a><span class="by-author"> by <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="https://upstarthr.com/author/admin/" title="View all posts by Ben" rel="author">Ben</a></span></span>.								</footer><!-- .entry-meta -->
	</article><!-- #post -->
							
	<article id="post-12825" class="post-12825 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general">
				<header class="entry-header">
			
						<h1 class="entry-title">
				<a href="https://upstarthr.com/were-only-human-47-using-mission-focused-learning-to-improve-learner-engagement/" rel="bookmark">We&#8217;re Only Human 47: Using Mission-Focused Learning to Improve Learner Engagement</a>
			</h1>
										<div class="comments-link">
					<a href="https://upstarthr.com/were-only-human-47-using-mission-focused-learning-to-improve-learner-engagement/#respond"><span class="leave-reply">Leave a reply</span></a>				</div><!-- .comments-link -->
					</header><!-- .entry-header -->

				<div class="entry-content">
			<p><iframe id='audio_iframe' src='https://www.podbean.com/media/player/uc48y-a45a21?skin=1&#038;download=0&#038;share=1&#038;auto=0&#038;fonts=Helvetica&#038;version=1&#038;btn-skin=107' data-link='https://www.podbean.com/media/player/uc48y-a45a21?skin=1&#038;download=0&#038;share=1&#038;auto=0&#038;fonts=Helvetica&#038;version=1&#038;btn-skin=107' height='122' width='100%' frameborder='0' scrolling='no' data-name='pb-iframe-player' ></iframe></p>
<p>Recent research from CLO Media shows that the number one performance metric reported by Chief Learning Officers for learning initiatives is employee engagement. But is this the right metric? Does engagement truly encapsulate how people learn, the impact on the business, and other critical factors? </p>
<p>To answer this question, host Ben Eubanks sits down with Sam Herring, VP and General Manager for Intrepid by VitalSource. Sam has a long track record in learning technology and services and a well-rounded outlook on the profession. In the conversation, Ben and Sam talk about the pros and cons of engagement as a learning metric, how mission-focused learning can lead to better results, and the importance of learning journeys. </p>
<p>If your team is thinking about how learning can partner more closely with the business this year and in the future, Sam&#8217;s insightful takeaways at the end of the show offer some spectacular guidance to that end. </p>
<p>Follow Sam on Twitter: <a href="https://twitter.com/samuelherring">https://twitter.com/samuelherring</a></p>
<p>Check out Intrepid Learning online: <a href="https://www.intrepidlearning.com/learning-library">https://www.intrepidlearning.com/learning-library</a> </p>
<p>Check out Ben&#8217;s newly released book, Artificial Intelligence for HR: <a href="http://aihrbook.com/buy">http://aihrbook.com/buy</a> </p>
					</div><!-- .entry-content -->
		
		<footer class="entry-meta">
			This entry was posted in <a href="https://upstarthr.com/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a> on <a href="https://upstarthr.com/were-only-human-47-using-mission-focused-learning-to-improve-learner-engagement/" title="7:34 am" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2019-01-14T07:34:37+00:00">January 14, 2019</time></a><span class="by-author"> by <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="https://upstarthr.com/author/admin/" title="View all posts by Ben" rel="author">Ben</a></span></span>.								</footer><!-- .entry-meta -->
